<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-096-520  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 096 520.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  Feb 20 1989 n208 p21(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Northrop rolls out paperless airplane. (F-A 18 Hornet) (NorthropCorp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pelton, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Northrop Corp is delivering its 842nd Hornet fighter jet toMcDonnell Douglas with 36 microfiche cards weighing six ounces,instead of the usual 16,000 pages of documentation weighing 240pounds.andP;  This marks the beginning of Northrup's plan to produceproducts through a paperless system.andP;  The new system has 1,000supervisors, assemblers, and quality assurance personnel workingfrom 135 screens on a quarter-mile assembly line connected to aTandem system.andP;  Engineers can now make product design changes in30 seconds, instead of two hours.andP;  The company estimates that the$10 million Integrated Management, Planning, and Control forAssembly (Impca) program will save the company around $20 million.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Northrop Corp. (automation).andO;Ticker:    NOC.andO;Topic:     Automated DocumentationProductionMicroficheAircraft.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>